==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: internet
<hw>in"ter*net</hw> <pr>(⟦icr⟧n"t⟦etil⟧r*n⟦ecr⟧t)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<def>A large network{3} of numerous computers connected through a number
of major nodes of high-speed computers having high-speed communications
channels between the major nodes, and numerous minor nodes allowing
electronic communication among millions of computers around the world;
-- usually referred to as <altname>the internet</altname>. It is the
basis for the <contr>World-Wide Web</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Interneural</ent>⟦br⟧
